in/img/my_logo_450.png">
            <h5>A JavaScript tool that translates any language into Pig Lat=
in.</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class=3D"section values">
      <div class=3D"container">
        <form>
          <div class=3D"row">
            <div class=3D"six columns">
              <label for=3D"exampleMessage">Type a phrase you need translat=
ed into Pig Latin</label>
              <textarea rows=3D"6" cols=3D"50" class=3D"u-full-width pigInp=
ut" id=3D"pigInput" type=3D"text" placeholder=3D"This text will be converte=
d into Pig Latin" name=3D"pigInput"></textarea>

              <a class=3D"button button-primary">Translate</a>
            </div>
            <div class=3D"six columns" id=3D"translation">
            </div>
          </div>

        </form>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class=3D"section get-help">
      <div class=3D"container">
          <div class=3D"row">
            <div class=3D"six columns">
              <h3>Basically, the Pig Latin system used here works as follow=
s:</h3>
              <p>You take the first letter of a word (e.g. Hello =3D H) and=
 use the last letters (e.g. Hello =3D ello) and add 'ay' to the first lette=
r (e.g. Hello =3D Ello hay).</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Words that start with a vowel (A, E, I, O, U) simply ha=
ve "ay" appended to the end of the word. Examples are:</li>
                  <ul>
                    <li>"eat" =E2=86=92 "eatay"</li>
                    <li>"omelet" =E2=86=92 "omeletay"</li>
                    <li>"are" =E2=86=92 "areay"</li>
                  </ul>
              </ul>

            </div>

            <div class=3D"six columns">
              <ul>
                <li>Words that start with a consonant have all consonant le=
tters up to the first vowel moved to the end of the word (as opposed to jus=
t the first consonant letter), and "-ay" is appended. -('Y' is counted as a=
 vowel in this context). Examples are:</li>
                  <ul>
                    <li>"pig" =E2=86=92 "ig-pay"</li>
                    <li>"banana" =E2=86=92 "anana-bay"</li>
                    <li>"trash" =E2=86=92 "ash-tray"</li>
                    <li>"happy" =E2=86=92 "appy-hay"</li>
                    <li>"duck" =E2=86=92 "uck-day"</li>
                    <li>"glove" =E2=86=92 "ove-glay"</li>
                  </ul>
              </ul>

            </div>
          </div>

       =20
      </div>
    </div>

